    </section>

    <!-- ─────────────── VI. License ─────────────── -->
    <section class="chap" id="license">
      <p class="chap-num">VI</p>
      <h2>License considerations</h2>
      <p>
        The font's <code>name</code> table carries the donor license attestation in machine-readable form. Most of the font is OFL 1.1; one large set of codepoints (the CJK ideographs sourced from FSung) carries a custom non-commercial restriction that propagates forward. See <a href="/license">/license</a> for the full text.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>For non-commercial use</strong> (research, education, personal reading, this website) the entire TTC is freely usable.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>For commercial products</strong> the TTC and per-plane TTFs are usable EXCEPT the CJK ideograph portion derived from FSung. The build's name table flags which glyphs carry the FSung non-commercial restriction; products that redistribute commercially must either (a) substitute an alternate CJK donor (Noto Sans CJK for example) or (b) exclude FSung-derived glyphs and ship a partial font.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>For embedding in distributed binaries</strong>: include <code>LICENSE.txt</code> with your artifact and the per-donor attribution file <code>LICENSE-SOURCES.md</code> (both ship in <a href="https://github.com/essenfont/essenfont/releases">each release</a>).
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- ─────────────── VII. Troubleshooting ─────────────── -->
    <section class="chap" id="troubleshooting">
      <p class="chap-num">VII</p>
      <h2>When something doesn't render</h2>
      <p>
        Failure modes the build's per-block subset script has all handled at least once. The full list is at <a href="/engineering/coverage">/engineering/coverage</a>; common ones:
      </p>
